    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='[{"url": "https://qapita.com/blog/409a-valuation-methodology-process", "title": "409A Valuation Methodology and Process Explained", "content": "The primary methods for 409A valuation include the Market Approach, Income Approach, and Asset Approach. The Market Approach compares the company to similar public companies, while the Income Approach uses projected future cash flows. The Asset Approach evaluates the company\'s net asset value. The choice of method depends on the company\'s stage, industry, and available data.\\n\\n### 2. How to learn 409A valuation?", "score": 0.72907686, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.qapita.com/blog/409a-valuation-%20methodology-process%E2%80%8B", "title": "409A Valuation Methodology and Process Explained", "content": "The primary methods for 409A valuation include the Market Approach, Income Approach, and Asset Approach. The Market Approach compares the company to similar public companies, while the Income Approach uses projected future cash flows. The Asset Approach evaluates the company\'s net asset value. The choice of method depends on the company\'s stage, industry, and available data.\\n\\n### 2. How to learn 409A valuation?", "score": 0.72907686, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.harness.co/articles/409a-valuation-how-it-works-and-common-questions", "title": "409A Valuation: How it Works and Common Questions | Harness", "content": "2. Probability-Weighted Expected Return Methodology (PWERM): PWERM estimates the fair value of each share of stock by considering various future scenarios of an IPO, merger or acquisition, or continued private operations. For each potential scenario, a probability is assigned based on the likelihood of each occurring. The expected value of the company\\u2019s equity is then calculated by weighting the potential outcomes by their respective probabilities and considering the present value of each", "score": 0.55796635, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://promise.legal/resources/409a-calculator", "title": "409A Valuation Calculator & Guide (2025) - Promise Legal", "content": "New funding round (SAFE, convertible, priced round)\\n Acquisition offer or term sheet\\n IPO preparation (S-1 filing)\\n Significant revenue change (2x growth or 50%+ decline)\\n Major product launch, pivot, or business model change\\n\\n### Typical 409A Cadence by Stage", "score": 0.47738418, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.esofund.com/blog/fair-market-value-fmv-409a", "title": "What Is FMV? 409A Valuations & Fair Market Value Explained", "content": "The FMV is determined by a 409a Valuation which is required by law to be updated every 12 months or any time a company closes a funding round. It is calculated either by the company internally or by an independent firm. The 409a will be valued based on similar publicly traded companies, the company\'s cash flows, or the company\'s assets - typically a mix of all.\\n\\n## What is a 409a valuation?", "score": 0.45391592, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://seedlegals.com/resources/409a-valuation", "title": "409A valuation: requirements and rules | SeedLegals", "content": "information about the specialist who created the valuation for your company.  Valuation methodology: A detailed explanation of the methods and approaches used to determine the fair market value (FMV) of your company\\u2019s stock.  Reporting and compliance: Proof that your company complies with the specific requirements of Section 409A of the Internal Revenue Code, including documenting the process, assumptions, and procedures used in the valuation, as well as confirmation that your company adheres", "score": 0.43611822, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://esofund.com/blog/fair-market-value-fmv-409a", "title": "What is a 409a Valuation (Fair Market Value)?", "content": "What is a 409a Valuation (Fair Market Value)?", "score": 0.4129331, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://etonvs.com/409a-valuation/409a-material-event-tender-offer-impact", "title": "409A Material Event - Impact of a Tender Offer on 409A FMV - Eton Venture Services", "content": "The article provides a quick look at the impact of a tender offer on the 409A Fair Market Value (FMV) and the criteria used to assess whether it is considered a 409A material event. A tender offer is a type of secondary sale or purchase of securities, typically common stock, made by an investor, group of investors, or a third party. If the tender offer is deemed a 409A material event, the existing 409A FMV report may become outdated and require an updated report. In order to determine if the", "score": 0.39277983, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://dimovtax.com/navigating-409a-valuation-for-private-companies-going-public-or-considering-a-tender-offer", "title": "Navigating 409A Valuation for Private Companies Going Public or Considering a Tender Offer - Dimov Tax & CPA Services", "content": "Due Diligence: In the context of a tender offer or acquisition, accurate 409A valuations help potential investors or acquirers assess the target company\\u2019s financial health and the value of its assets, liabilities, and equity.\\n Tax Planning: Going public or participating in a tender offer can have significant tax implications. Accurate 409A valuations assist in tax planning, helping companies and employees optimize their tax positions and minimize tax liabilities.", "score": 0.3900581, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://eqvista.com/409a-valuation/409a-valuation-for-llc", "title": "409a valuation for LLC - A Complete Guide | Eqvista", "content": "A 409A valuation determines the fair market value of a company\\u2019s common shares. This assessment will allow you to pay employees fair market value for equity-based remuneration such as stock options, restricted shares, and other share-based equity instruments. Section 409A of the United States Internal Revenue Law (the \\u201ctax code\\u201d) is the source of this valuation\\u2019s name, and mandates that options issued as remuneration to service providers (employees or non-employees) have an exercise price equal", "score": 0.38366494, "raw_content": null}]',
